<div id="review_31618153" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/31618153" />
    <a title="Ginger" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/133022-ginger"><img alt="Ginger" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1519763585p2/133022.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/31618153?book_show_action=true">Aug 30, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ginger" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ginger" href="/user/show/133022-ginger">Ginger</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/133022-ginger?shelf=middle-grade">middle-grade</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/133022-ginger?shelf=ya">ya</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/133022-ginger?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/133022-ginger?shelf=books-by-friends">books-by-friends</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer31618153" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9266269704213242778">The Amaranth Enchantment, Julie Berry&apos;s debut novel, has the shadow of a fairy tale in its soul. Yes, there&apos;s a prince, but not just any prince; this prince looks like he swallowed the sun for breakfast. Yes, there&apos;s a royal ball, but not just any royal ball; this ball is to announce the engagement of the prince to a princess who looks like she was sculpted from spun sugar. And then there&apos;s our heroine, Lucinda Chapdelaine, who has not only wit, but compassion as well, not to mention brains and </span>
  <span id="freeText9266269704213242778" style="display:none">The Amaranth Enchantment, Julie Berry's debut novel, has the shadow of a fairy tale in its soul. Yes, there's a prince, but not just any prince; this prince looks like he swallowed the sun for breakfast. Yes, there's a royal ball, but not just any royal ball; this ball is to announce the engagement of the prince to a princess who looks like she was sculpted from spun sugar. And then there's our heroine, Lucinda Chapdelaine, who has not only wit, but compassion as well, not to mention brains and beauty, too. Add to this mix a rogue of a street thief, a faithful goat named Dog, a bit of magic, a maligned woman, and an immortal villain and you get a delightful and well-written read. Highly recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9266269704213242778" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


