    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_54833014" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/54833014" />
    <a title="Brooke Shirts" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/905998-brooke-shirts"><img alt="Brooke Shirts" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1204068127p2/905998.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/54833014?book_show_action=true">May 03, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brooke Shirts" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brooke Shirts" href="/user/show/905998-brooke-shirts">Brooke Shirts</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer54833014" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16397770674134839330">A fairy-tale-esque story in the style of Gail Carson Levine. Lucinda is a girl who has gone from riches to rags after the mysterious death of her aristocratic parents, and now lives at the mercy of her shrewish aunt and uncle, who run a jewelry shop. When a mysterious woman --the legendary Amaranth Witch -- gives a magical stone to her uncle for safekeeping, Lucinda suddenly finds herself caught in a plot involving the witch, one rogue of a cute thief, a handsome prince, and a sinister sorcerer </span>
  <span id="freeText16397770674134839330" style="display:none">A fairy-tale-esque story in the style of Gail Carson Levine. Lucinda is a girl who has gone from riches to rags after the mysterious death of her aristocratic parents, and now lives at the mercy of her shrewish aunt and uncle, who run a jewelry shop. When a mysterious woman --the legendary Amaranth Witch -- gives a magical stone to her uncle for safekeeping, Lucinda suddenly finds herself caught in a plot involving the witch, one rogue of a cute thief, a handsome prince, and a sinister sorcerer from an alternate world. Oh, and did I mention the handsome prince?<br /><br />The book was cute and enjoyable -- Berry has a knack for funny dialogue and threw in plot twists that kept me on my toes. However, it bothered me that the minor characters frequently mentioned how kind and giving the protagonist was, while it seemed to me that Lucinda rarely acted out of anything but her own self-interest. Some of the minor characters could have used more depth, and the witch is given a backstory that takes a definite Turn for the Weird. The plot is resolved with a prince-and-pauper scheme that I found hard to swallow. <br /><br />But, whatever -- I still found it a whole lot of fun, and most junior high aged kids likely will, too. More books with Peter the Thief, please!</span>
  <a data-text-id="16397770674134839330" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


