            <span class="readable">&ldquo;I don't suppose you believe love could last forever."<br />I'd hurt him. I looked away, chagrined.<br />"You're mistaken," I said. "I do believe it could. But it would depend upon the lovers."<br />He folded his arms and watched me, forcing me to return his gaze. Oh, those eyes.<br />"And what kind of lovers must they be?" he asked.<br />The You-and-Me kind?&rdquo;</span>
